11. Interview Explanation (30–60 sec)

> A brute-force solution tries all insertion positions and all 26 letters, recomputing the LCS every time, which is expensive. The optimized solution precomputes two DP tables: a prefix LCS table and a suffix LCS table. For each insertion position and each character occurrence in s2, we check whether pre[pos][j] + 1 + suf[pos][j+1] equals the original LCS plus one. If it does, that character can be inserted at that position. A set prevents duplicate counting for repeated characters. This reduces the overall complexity to O(n1 × n2).




