12. Key Takeaways

Classic application of Prefix + Suffix DP.

Avoid repeated LCS computation.

Use two DP tables.

Remove duplicates using a set.

Final complexity is O(n1 × n2).



---

13. Common Mistakes

Recomputing LCS after every insertion.

Forgetting insertion at the beginning or end.

Counting duplicate characters multiple times.

Building the suffix DP in the wrong direction.

Using pre[pos][j+1] instead of pre[pos][j].

Forgetting the inserted character contributes exactly 1.



